                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Good for you!  You group with perfect people.  Yay?  The majority of people will end up grouping with strangers at some point, and have to work with it as best they can.  Yeah, sometimes that means lying.  I'm sorry you're incapable of saying to hold pulls when you need to, or unable to report your mana if asked.  Most of us don't have that problem, though, so I really can't see how tailoring the game to the one person in the world who plays with perfect people, yet is incapable of reporting their mana or asking for a hold when needed, yet whose perfect friends require this information, is going to help anything.
<br />

<br />
The majority don't want it.  The vast majority dont' want it or don't care about it.  Why would you listen to the minority when the majority have made their feelings quite clear?  And especially when the minority are people who CLAIM they are such great players that mana doesn't matter... if it doesn't matter, why do you need to see it when it will create serious problems for others?
<br />

<br />
Obviously, it has caused tremendous hardship so far, and made it impossible to group...  <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
But yeah, I posted polls, and there's a nice long thread going on to discuss it.  I posted here the majority opinion according to those polls.  Feel free to say how perfect your friends all are in the other thread.  I don't really see how that's "information" that refutes polls which state the majority  over all are are against it or impartial to it.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=391428" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: purple">Magelo</span></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
