                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think showing mana is a bad thing, because the information isn't reliable.
<br />

<br />
There is too much difference in the mana regen and mana pools between toons to be able to properly judge them based off the percentage of mana they have remaining.
<br />

<br />
It also has no regard for group composition and play style.  If I am not slowing and am playing conductor at Grand Central Station then I am usually close to  full mana til the train shows up.  I don't want to take crap from arm chair enchanters that I am not doing my job because I have too much mana.  Especially not when I am having to keep spells like mem blur up becuase the tank is an idiot and can't break mez properly.
<br />

<br />
Similar arguments could be made for the current display of the health bars.  However, the levels of party health are almost solely the responsibility of the parties healer and it is rare for a party to dictate how a healer does their job.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
