                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It's all about group communication. Weather you are grouping with complete strangers, or a normal group of friends. 
<br />

<br />
If you are in an intensive group non stop pulling, communicate where you are in mana. Let the group know. But as most have said, this is your choice to let them know. Not someone else's determination of where the little blue bar is.
<br />

<br />
Doesn't matter to me one way or the other. If I get LoM, and tell them to hold pulls because I just had to C5/Haste/God/Tash/Mez/Slow and Remez because some idiot does not know how to assist.. And they continue pulling.. I'll sit there and med and let them fight the mob unslowed until I am okay with mana.. Then again.. I'm usally pulling, so that doesn't come into play much..  <img src="images/smiles/icon_surprised.gif" alt="icon_surprised.gif" border="0" /> 
