                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Others being able to see how much mana I have would be a great thing, if I could shut it off at will. Sometimes I STILL want to get asked, "rfp?" rather than someone deciding on their own if I'm ready. But then when I trust the people I'm with, if they could see my mana it would make things go much faster and smoother and eliminate a lot of typing and potential miscommunication.
<br />

<br />
Those of you who NEVER want anyone to know how much mana you have....sorry, I don't get it. But hey, whatever.
<br />

<br />
How about a /reportmana command? Sends an automatic tell from you, to either group or raid, what your mana level is. It could be the best of both worlds for people who still want to keep it anonymous but will tell how much they have if asked. It could be 2 versions, /greportmana and /rsreportmana for group and raid.
<br />

<br />
"But that won't work, I need to be able to fib a little bit. I want them to think I have less mana than i actually have so I can keep a reserve."  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_liar.gif" alt="eusa_liar.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I understand this sentiment completely. Add a little modifier to the command.../greportmana-25 would tell your group you're at 10 mana when you're actually at 35.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
For those who don't like /reportmana...how about /showmana-25? Essentially the same thing, except your turning your viewable mana bar on with the modifier. Your group or raid veiwable mana bar would always appear to have 25% less mana than it actually does. They could add in a feature that makes the bar seem to regen to 100 when you've been sitting to a few minutes, then drop to [100 minus modifier number minus the mana you just used] when you first start casting again so that your group members don't catch on to the trick.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="icon_twisted.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Deezle on Fri Jun 18, 2004 12:24 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
